  {
    "action": {
      "input": {
        "description": " A turnkey commercial entity for agents that enables builder teams to combine development and early commercial activity under a single legal structure. It serves as a coordination hub for contributors and customers, enabling teams to process revenues and expenses, contract with customers, and manage early sales without incurring in structural overhead.\n\nTypical Use Cases\n\n- Early products moving from grants to revenue\n- Teams testing initial commercial demand\n- One\u2011entity setups before fundraising or regulatory complexity\n\nSuitable for Early\u2011stage teams with no external funding and limited regulatory exposure, where simplicity outweighs structural separation.\n\n**Capabilities**\n\n\u2705 Receive income in crypto as grants or donations\n\n\u2705Pay and hire contributors\n\n\u2705Pay out dividends\n\n\u2705Issue shares, security tokens, and receive external investment\n\n\u2705Getting a bank account\n\n\u2705Public Registry requirement\n\n\ud83d\udfe8International Team (founding team may be abroad, but a local Director is  required)\n\n\ud83d\udfe8Tax optimization\n\n\ud83d\udfe8Shareholder anonymity (depends on final entity type)\n\n",
        "lastModified": "2026-04-03T10:59:39.000Z",
        "summary": "A single legal entity to build, commercialize, and operate a product from day one.\n",
        "title": "Commercial Operational Hub (OH)"
      },
